# Build or Install ST Sopwith

Sopwith can be installed using the following instructions.

## Atari ST

You can download the latest version of ST Sopwith from
https://github.com/neilrackett/atarist-sopwith/releases

The quickest way to build it yourself is to install atarist-toolkit-docker
and run

    stcmd make

This will build SOPWITH.TOS into the build directory.

## SDL

While this repo is focussed on the Atari ST version of Sopwith,
it is still possible to build the SDL version:

    ./autogen.sh && make VARIANT=sdl

Optionally you can then either run a local copy of Sopwith using:

    build-sdl/src/sopwith

Or install the program by running

    sudo make VARIANT=sdl install
